Class AbstractSharedValue

    AbstractNumericDataSource, AbstractNumericFunction, SharedBoolean, SharedFunction, SharedInteger, SharedReal, SharedString, SharedTable
    public abstract class AbstractSharedValue
extends AbstractBeanComponent
    The base class for shared values: components whose value may be referenced by attributes in other components, subblocks, etc.

      • setNameConstrained

        public void setNameConstrained​(java.lang.String val_)
        Sets the name of this value. Names must be non-null, non-empty, and match the regular expression stored in NAME_REGEX_STANDARD. No two values falling under the umbrella of AbstractNumericsModel.CAT_SHARED_VALUE may have the same name. The legacy naming convention is suppored through NAME_REGEX_LEGACY for models that use it.

      • getNextDefaultName

        public static java.lang.String getNextDefaultName​(AbstractSharedValue variable,
                                                  java.lang.String prefix,
                                                  Category category)
        Gets the name of the given variable based on the given prefix and the names of the variables in the given category. For example, specifying a prefix of "r" while the model contains variables "r1" and "r3" will result in a new name of "r4". Case is ignored when comparing the prefix.
        Parameters:
        prefix - a String containing the portion of the name to search on. Names that contain only this prefix and a trailing positive number will affect the new name. This prefix must be safe for use as part of a regular expression

                                               java.lang.String name)

        name - the name of the component to find
        Returns:

      • getIterationCount

        public int getIterationCount()
        Returns the number of parametric iterations that must be performed to access all parametric values. This is NOT the index of the current iteration. This method may not operate in constant time, therefore the value should be cached when needed for repeat access. The default implementation returns 0.
